message.content:
There are a few different ways to say "cheers" in Scottish Gaelic:

1. Slàinte mhath! (pronounced: slan-je vah) - Good health!
2. Mòran taing! (pronounced: mawr-an tine) - Many thanks!

These two phrases are used interchangeably as a toast or a cheers expression, so you can choose the one that best fits the situation or context.
